## First preflight run

Status: failed, then fixed. This run proved the Nix shell could realize the new
Wayland/GBM packages and exposed an incorrect generated protocol symbol in the
initial preflight source.

```sh
nix develop -c just direct-capture-preflight
```

Key result:

```text
error: 'ext_output_image_capture_source_manager_v1_interface' undeclared
```

## Protocol dependency inspection

Status: passed.

```sh
nix develop -c bash -lc 'protocol_dir=$(pkg-config --variable=pkgdatadir wayland-protocols); tmp=$(mktemp -d); wayland-scanner client-header "$protocol_dir/staging/ext-image-copy-capture/ext-image-copy-capture-v1.xml" "$tmp/ext.h"; grep -n "interface" "$tmp/ext.h" | head -60; rm -rf "$tmp"'
nix develop -c bash -lc 'protocol_dir=$(pkg-config --variable=pkgdatadir wayland-protocols); find "$protocol_dir" -name "*capture*source*.xml" -o -name "*image*capture*.xml" | sort'
nix develop -c bash -lc 'protocol_dir=$(pkg-config --variable=pkgdatadir wayland-protocols); grep -n "foreign_toplevel\|import" "$protocol_dir/staging/ext-image-capture-source/ext-image-capture-source-v1.xml"; find "$protocol_dir" -name "*foreign*toplevel*.xml" -print'
```

Key results:

```text
ext-image-copy-capture-v1 exports ext_image_copy_capture_manager_v1_interface.
wayland-protocols 1.48 provides staging/ext-image-capture-source/ext-image-capture-source-v1.xml.
ext-image-capture-source-v1 references ext_foreign_toplevel_handle_v1.
wayland-protocols 1.48 provides staging/ext-foreign-toplevel-list/ext-foreign-toplevel-list-v1.xml.
```

